			<h4><strong>Visteon Electronics Tunisia Overview</strong></h4>
				<p>
					Visteon Electronics Tunisia Bir El Bey Plant has reached a Visteon benchmark manufacturing location with more than 400 highly skilled, engaged and ethical employees. The manufacturing area is equipped with:
                    <ul class = "square">
                        <li>Three Standard SMT lines with continuous Lean concepts and high-volume components, last generation chip shooter, Pick & Place machines and 3D SPI & AOI machines. All the lines are dual-lane types and can produce double-side reflow printed circuit boards, allowing more efficient space use and lower energy consumption.</li>
                        <li>Eight Mono & Bi-Material injection machines that produce more than 12,000 parts per day.</li>
                        <li>Twenty assembly lines with customized solutions for each product and customer and high content of poka yoke systems that produce 48,000 parts per day. The plant has an extend Know How in Winding, on-line Heat Sealing and Pointer Insertion Process, among others. For inspection, they are using Color Vision system in most of the assembly lines.</li>
                    </ul>
				</p>
        <p>
            The large product portfolio includes: displays & multimedia, clocks, parking systems, key fobs, immobilizers and compasses to ensure a strong and growing customer base.
        </p>
        <h4><strong>Plant Vision and Mission</strong></h4>
        <p>
          The plant’s vision is to create a first-class Visteon manufacturing location with a highly skilled, engaged and ethical team to satisfy customers with high-quality and high-tech processes. For that, the management team continuously empowers all employees to provide solutions for customers and to build a network of sustainable, mutually beneficial business relationships. The mission is to transform operators into cultural change agents, always seeking for improvement, and to engage team members to create the sense of process ownership to the operator level. 
        </p>  
        <p>
            The key success tool is the self-directed work teams deployed through all departments and involving all employees at all levels with a primary mission of waste elimination and process performance improvement. According to the last employee survey, 98% of employees have a deep understanding of customer wants and needs; they confirm that they are able to meet short-term demands without compromising their long-term vision.
        </p>
